A handful of enthusiastic cyclists gathered at the Bendor Shopping Complex for a 63 km charity ride to Ga-Phago village in Moletjie on Sunday. Coordinator Shaun Ramathlodi, front right, show the team s readiness to deliver among others sanitary pads, non-perishable food and clothes to the children of the village. It was a wonderful experience to do what we love and in return give back to the community, Ramatlhodi said. Story and photo: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com &nbsp;